TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Comm Spawn
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
if not Spring.GetModOptions().commandertypes then GG.mission.ExecuteTriggerByName("Spawn Comm Fallback") else local teamID = 0 local teamInfo = teamID and select(7, Spring.GetTeamInfo(teamID)) if teamInfo and teamInfo.staticcomm then local commanderName = teamInfo.staticcomm local commanderLevel = teamInfo.staticcomm_level or 1 local commanderProfile = GG.ModularCommAPI.GetCommProfileInfo(commanderName) local startUnit = commanderProfile.baseUnitDefID
local x, z = 5000, 3580 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) local unitID = GG.DropUnit(startUnit, x, y, z, 0, teamID, _, _, _, _, _, GG.ModularCommAPI.GetProfileIDByBaseDefID(startUnit), teamInfo and tonumber(teamInfo.static_level), true) Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, Spring.GetGaiaTeamID(), false) -- Gaia GG.mission.AddUnitGroup(unitID,"Comm") end end

TriggerLogic.Name: Transfer Gaia to Gaia
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Gaia") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, Spring.GetGaiaTeamID(), false) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Force Start
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
Spring.SendCommands("info 0")
-- force start when testing from Mission Editor -- not needed if run from Chobby campaign (a widget will do this) if not Spring.GetModOptions().commandertypes then --Spring.SendCommands("forcestart") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Give Fire Orders (custom)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("tankarty") local enemies = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("enemygrizz2") local target for unitID,_ in pairs(enemies) do target = unitID end
if target then for unitID,_ in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.ATTACK, {target}, 0) end end
--local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("paladin") --local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) --x = x + 1300 --Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.DGUN, {x, y, z}, 0)

TriggerLogic.Name: Ally Factory Guard
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
include("LuaRules/Configs/customcmds.h.lua")
local rectangleUnits = Spring.GetUnitsInRectangle(4300, 3000, 5800, 4200) if rectangleUnits then local factoryID for i = 1, #rectangleUnits do local unitDefID = Spring.GetUnitDefID(rectangleUnits[i]) local ud = unitDefID and UnitDefs[unitDefID] if ud and ud.name == "factorycloak" then factoryID = rectangleUnits[i] break end end if factoryID then local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("spidercon") if units then for unitID,_ in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.GUARD, {factoryID}, {}) end end end end
